Dataset Structure & Metadata

The Shield Insurance Analysis project uses 6 core datasets stored inside the `/Datasets/` folder. These datasets support customer analysis, revenue tracking, policy performance, time intelligence, and settlement analysis.

1. dim_customer.csv
Contains customer demographic details such as customer ID, age, age group, birth date, and city information including Delhi NCR, Mumbai, Hyderabad, Chennai, and Indore.

2. dim_policies.csv
Stores insurance policy information including policy IDs, coverage details, and premium-related information for all insurance products.

3. dim_date.csv
Standard date dimension table used for calendar analysis, monthly trends, weekdays/weekends, and week-based reporting.

4. DateTable.csv
Advanced calendar table created for Power BI time intelligence, proper month sorting, and DAX calculations.

5. fact_premiums.csv
Main transactional dataset containing premium transactions, customer IDs, policy IDs, sales modes, transaction dates, and revenue amounts.

6. fact_settlements.csv
Contains settlement and risk analysis data including age-based settlement percentages and claim-related risk metrics.

These datasets are connected using a dimensional data model to support efficient reporting and dashboard analysis in Power BI.
